ernaum\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 45\" | 2018\n| S\u00e3o Paulo International Film Festival\n| Best Feature Film\n| Capernaum\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 45\" | 2018\n| S\u00e3o Paulo International Film Festival\n| Best Foreign Fiction\n| Capernaum\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 46\" | 2017\n| Chicago Film Critics Association Awards\n| Best Foreign Language Fiction\n| Capernaum\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 47\" | 2012\n| Murex D'Or\n| Best Lebanese Film Award\n| Where Do We Go Now? \n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 48\" | 2011\n| Cannes Film Festival\n| Prize of the Ecumenical Jury - Special Mention\n| Where Do We Go Now?\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 49\" | 2011\n| Cannes Film Festival\n| Fran\u00e7ois Chalais Award\n| Where Do We Go Now?\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 50\" | 2011\n| Cannes Film Festival\n| Un Certain Regard Award\n| Where Do We Go Now?\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 51\" | 2011\n| Oslo Films from the South Festival\n| Audience Award\n| Where Do We Go Now?\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 52\" | 2011\n| Oslo Films from the South Festival\n| Silver Mirror Award\n| Where Do We Go Now?\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 53\" | 2011\n| San Sebasti\u00e1n International Film Festival\n| Best European Film\n| Where Do We Go Now?\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 54\" | 2011\n| Stockholm Film Festival\n| Best Script\n| Where Do We Go Now?\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 55\" | 2011\n| Stockholm Film Festival\n| Best Film\n| Where Do We Go Now?\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 56\" | 2011\n| Toronto International Film Festival\n| People's Choice Award\n| Where Do We Go Now?\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 54\" | 2009\n| Argentinean Film Critics Association Awards\n| Best Foreign Film, Not in the Spanish Language\n| Caramel\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 55\" | 2008\n| Dublin Film Critics Circle Awards\n| Best Actress\n| Caramel\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 57\" | 2008\n| Dublin Film Critics Circle Awards\n| Breakthrough Artist\n| Caramel\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 58\" | 2007\n| Asia Pacific Screen Awards\n| Achievement in Directing\n| Caramel\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 59\" | 2007\n| Asia Pacific Screen Awards\n| Best Performance by an Actress\n| Caramel\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 60\" | 2007\n| Cannes Film Festival\n| Golden Camera\n| Caramel\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 61\" | 2007\n| Cannes Film Festival\n| C.I.C.A.E. Award\n| Caramel\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 62\" | 2007\n| Oslo Films from the South Festival\n| Best Feature\n| Caramel\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 63\" | 2007\n| San Sebasti\u00e1n International Film Festival\n| Audience Award\n| Caramel\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 64\" | 2007\n| San Sebasti\u00e1n International Film Festival\n| Youth Jury Award\n| Caramel\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 65\" | 2007\n| San Sebasti\u00e1n International Film Festival\n| Sebastiane Award\n| Caramel\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 66\" | 2007\n| Stockholm Film Festival\n| FIPRESCI Prize\n| Caramel\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row 67\" | 2007\n| Paris Biennal of Arab Cinema\n| Best Short Film - Fiction \n| 11 Rue Pasteur\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Nadine Labaki\"/>\n|-\n\n== Other work ==\nIn 2014, Labaki was the goodwill ambassador for the bi-lingual and multimedia campaign produced by The Brave Heart Fund (BHF). Based out of the Children\u2019s Heart Center at the [[American University of Beirut]] Medical Center, the BHF creates awareness and helps to fund operations and procedures for under privileged children with Congenital Heart Disease.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.braveheartfund.org/newsDetail.php?id=426|title=News Details - Brave Heart|website=www.braveheartfund.org|access-date=2018-03-01}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.nadinelabaki.com}}\n* [http://www.facebook.com/NadineLabaki Official fan page]\n* {{IMDb name|id=1701024|name=Nadine Labaki}}\n\n{{Nadine Labaki}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Labaki, Nadine}}\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Lebanese women film directors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Lebanese actresses]]\n[[Category:Lebanese film directors]]\n[[Category:Lebanese Maronites]]\n[[Category:Lebanese screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Women screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Female music video directors]]\n[[Category:Saint Joseph University alumni]]\n[[Category:Lebanese film actresses]]\n[[Category:Lebanese music video directors]]\n[[Category:People from Matn District]]\n", "name_user": "Anomalocaris", "label": "safe", "comment": "properly close table (|}); improve <ref>s; improve <ref name>s; rm space before <ref> straight quotes and apostrophes; {{cite journal}} is only for footnoted academic articles; dashes; underprivileged one word", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nadine_Labaki"}
{"title_page": "Galmoy (barony)", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=January 2017}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| official_name           = Galmoy\n| native_name             = <small>''Gabhalmhaigh'' ([[Irish language|Irish]])<ref name=logainmGalmoy/><ref name=Government2003/></small><!-- if different from the English name -->\n| native_name_lang        = ga<!-- ISO 639-2 code e.g. \"fr\" for French. If more than one, use {{lang}} instead -->\n| other_name              = Barony of Galmoy\n| settlement_type         = [[Barony (Ireland)|Barony]]<!-- such as Town, Village, City, Borough etc. -->\n<!-- images, nickname, motto -->\n| image_skyline           =File:Urlingford,_County_Kilkenny.jpg\n| imagesize               = 260\n| image_alt               = 260\n| image_caption           = Aerial view of [[Urlingford]]\n| image_map                 = {{CSS image crop\n| Image = Ireland - 1885 Map of County Kilkenny.jpg\n| bSize = 650\n| oLeft = 40\n| oTop = 50\n| cWidth = 260\n| cHeight = 260\n| Location = center\n}}\n| map_caption = Map of Galmoy\n| etymology               = plain of the Branch, or Ghabhal ([[River Goul]])<ref name=Carrigan1905/>\n<!-- maps and coordinates -->\n| coordinates             = {{coord|52|46|6|N|7|30|57|W|dim:100000_region:IE|display=inline,title}}\n| pushpin_map             = Ireland\n| pushpin_label_position  = left\n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Ireland\n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[Provinces of Ireland|Province]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Leinster]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[Counties of Ireland|County]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[County Kilkenny]]\n<!-- established -->\n| established_title       = <!-- Founded -->\n| established_date        =\n| established_title1      = <!-- Incorporated (town) -->\n| established_date1       =\n| established_title2      = <!-- Incorporated (city) -->\n| established_date2       =\n| extinct_title           =\n| extinct_date            =\n| founder                 =\n| named_for               =\n<!-- seat, smaller parts -->\n| seat_type               = <!-- defaults to: Seat -->\n| seat                    =\n| seat1_type              = <!-- defaults to: Former seat -->\n| seat1                   =\n| parts_type              = [[Civil parishes in Ireland|Civil parishes]]<!-- defaults to: Boroughs -->\n| parts_style             = coll<!-- list, coll (collapsed list), para (paragraph format) -->\n| parts                   = <!-- parts text, or header for parts list -->\n| p1                      = Erke\n| p2                      = Aharney\n| p3                      = Urlingford\n| p4                      = Balleen\n| p5                      = Borrismore\n| p6                      = Coolcashin\n| p7                      = Durrow\n| p8                      = Fertagh\n| p9                      = Glashare\n| p10                     = Rathbeagh\n| p11                      =Rathlogan\n| p12                      =Sheffin\n<!-- government type, leaders -->\n| government_footnotes    =<ref name=KCC/><!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| government_type         =[[County Council]]\n| governing_body          =[[Kilkenny County Council]]\n| leader_party            =\n| leader_title            =\n| leader_name             = <!-- add &nbsp; (no-break space) to disable automatic links -->\n| leader_title1           =\n| leader_name1            = <!-- etc., up to leader_title4 / leader_name4 -->\n<!-- display settings -->\n<!-- area -->\n| area_footnotes          = <ref name=townlands.ie/><!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| area_total_km2          = 162.7\n<!-- elevation -->\n| elevation_footnotes     = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| elevation_m             =\n<!-- population -->\n| population_as_of        =\n| population_footnotes    = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| population_total        =\n| pop_est_as_of           =\n| pop_est_footnotes       =\n| population_est          =\n| population_rank         =\n| population_density_km2  = <!-- for automatic calculation of any density field, use: auto -->\n| population_density_sq_mi=\n| population_demonym      = <!-- demonym, e.g. Liverpudlian for someone from Liverpool -->\n| population_note         =\n<!-- time zone(s) -->\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n\n'''Galmoy''' ({{Irish place name|Gabhalmhaigh|plain of the [[River Goul|Ghabhal]] [River Goul]}})<ref name=logainmGalmoy/><ref name=Carrigan1905/> is a [[Barony (Ireland)|barony]] in the north western part of [[County Kilkenny]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]].<ref name=logainmGalmoy/><ref name=Tighe1802/>   It is one of 12 baronies in County Kilkenny.<ref name=Government2003/>  The size of the barony is {{convert|162.7|km2}}.<ref name=townlands.ie/> There are 12 [[Civil parishes in Ireland|civil parishes]] in Galmoy.<ref name=logainmGalmoy/>  While it is named after the village of [[Galmoy]], today the chief town of the barony is [[Urlingford]]. Galmoy barony lies at the north-western corner of the county between [[Fassadinin]] to the east (whose chief town is [[Castlecomer]]),  and [[Cranagh|Crannagh]] to the south (whose chief town is [[Freshford, County Kilkenny|Freshford]]). It is surrounded on two sides by counties Tipperary to the west and Laois to the north. The [[M8 motorway (Ireland)|M8]] Dublin/Cork motorway bisects the barony. It is situated {{convert|121|km|mi}} from [[Dublin]] city and {{convert|131|km|mi}} from [[Cork (city)|Cork]] city. Galmoy is currently administered by [[Kilkenny County Council]].<ref name=KCC/> The barony was part of in the historic kingdom of [[Osraige]] (''Ossory'').\n\n== History==\nThe name  of Galmoy, in Irish \"''Gabhalmhaigh''\", means \"''plain of the Branch, or Ghabhal ([[River Goul]])''\". The barony was part of in the historic kingdom of [[Osraige]] (''Ossory'') and was the territory of the [[Osraige#Ossorian clans|Ua Br\u00f3ithe]] clan.<ref name=walshGalmoy/><ref name=OHeerin1851/> According to O'Heerin's Topographical Poem (1420)<ref name=OHeerin1851/> at the time of the [[Norman invasion of Ireland|Norman invasion]] the area was the territory of the [[Irish Clan|clan]] called the Ua Br\u00f3ithe (O'Brophy) of Mag S\u00e9dna.<ref name=walshGalmoy/><ref name=OHeerin1851/>\n{{Quote box| quote =\"A fine district of beauteous nuts;<br /> O'Broithe over free Magh Sedna.\"|align=left |width=25%|source=\u2014[[Giolla na Naomh \u00d3 hUidhr\u00edn|\u00d3 hUidhr\u00edn]], ''[[Triallam timcheall na Fodla]]'' (''\"Let us wander around Ireland\"'') (1420).<ref name=OHeerin1851/><ref name=Carrigan1905/>}}\n\nIn a 1247 [[Vassal|feodary]] is Stephen Archid[ekne] holding 2 1/2 knights' fees in ''\"Gauleme\"'', spelled ''\"Ganelomey\"'' in the [[Calendar of Patent Rolls]].<ref name=Carrigan1905/><ref name=Brooks1950/>  In the 1324 feodary Raymond le Ercedekne, son of Richard, held the lands of Gavelmoy, in the barony of Galmoy.<ref name=Brooks1950/> Galmoy was recorded in the [[Down Survey]] (1656),<ref name=downGalmoy/> the 1840 Ordnance Survey Map<ref name=logainmOrdnanceSurvey/> and on Griffith's Valuation (1864).<ref name=Griffith/>\n\nThe main landholders in the barony were the [[Butler dynasty|Butlers]]. The [[Viscount Galmoye]] peers were descended from the [[Thomas Butler, 10th Earl of Ormond|10th Earl of Ormond]] (see [[Piers Butler, 3rd Viscount Galmoye]]). The O'Brophy's and Archdeacons were based in Galmoy.<ref name=Carrigan1905/><ref name=walshGalmoy/> It had been established by 1672. \n\nIn the 18th century County Kilkenny consisted of the Liberties of Kilkenny, and of Callan, and the baronies of Galmoy, Lower Ossory, Fassadinig, Cranagh, Shellilogher, Gowran, Kells, Knocktopher, Ida, Igrin, Iverk and Ibercon.<ref name=walshGalmoy/>  By the 19th century these were restructured into the baronies of Callan, Crannagh, Fassadinin, Galmoy, Gowran, Ida, Iverk, Kells, Knocktopher, and Shillelogher.<ref name=walshGalmoy/>  It was in the [[Poor law union]] of Urlingford.<ref name=Parliament/>\n\n== Geography==\n[[Image:RiverGoul1876-2.jpg|thumb|left|[[River Goul]] near village of [[Galmoy]].]]\n\nThe  county is subdivided into 12 [[barony (Ireland)|baronies]]<ref name=Government2003/> These include [[Kilkenny (barony)|Kilkenny]] in the centre of the county, and clockwise from north of the county, [[Fassadinin]], [[Gowran (barony)|Gowran]], [[Ida (barony)|Ida]], [[Kilculliheen]], [[Iverk]], [[Knocktopher (barony)|Knocktopher]], [[Kells (County Kilkenny barony)|Kells]], [[Callan (barony)|Callan]],  [[Shillelogher (barony)|Shillelogher]], [[Crannagh]],  [[Galmoy (barony)|Galmoy]].<ref name=logainmCountyKilkenny/>\n\nGalmoy contains the towns of [[Urlingford]], [[Johnstown, County Kilkenny|Johnstown]], and [[Ballyragget]], and the population centres of Crosspatrick, [[Galmoy]], Gattabaun.<ref name=logainmGalmoySettlements/> Galmoy is made up of 12 [[Civil parishes in Ireland|civil parishes]] of [[Erke, County Kilkenny|Erke]], [[Aharney]], [[Urlingford]] , [[Balleen, County Kilkenny|Balleen]], [[Borrismore]], [[Coolcashin]], [[Durrow, County Kilkenny|Durrow]], [[Fertagh]] ,  [[Glashare]],  [[Rathbeagh]], [[Rathlogan]], and [[Sheffin]]<ref name=logainmGalmoyParishes/> And these include 86 [[townlands]] (See [[List of townlands in County Kilkenny]]).\n\nKennedys Cross and Knockmannon Cross Roads are [[Crossroads (junction)|crossroads]] located in Galmoy.<ref name=logainmCrossroads/> Today it is part of the [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic Church]] diocese of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Ossory|Ossory]] and  the [[Church of Ireland]] diocese of [[Diocese of Cashel and Ossory|Cashel and Ossory]]. \n\n==Legal context==\nBaronies were created after the [[Norman invasion of Ireland]] as subdivisions of counties and were used for administration. While baronies continue to be officially defined units, they have been administratively obsolete since 1898. However, they continue to be used in land registration and specification such as in planning permissions. In many cases, a barony corresponds to an earlier [[Gaels|Gaelic]] t\u00faath which had submitted to the Crown.\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Ireland|Kilkenny}}\n\n*[[Barony (county division)]]\n*[[Barony (Ireland)]]\n* [[List of baronies of Ireland]]\n* [[List of townlands of County Kilkenny]]\n* [[List of Irish Local Government Areas 1900 - 1921]]\n\n==References==\n===Footnotes===\n<!-- Notes -->\n{{reflist|2|refs=\n\n<ref name=Government2003>\n({{Harvnb|Government|2003}})\n</ref>\n<ref name=logainmGalmoy>\n({{Harvnb|Fiontar|2008|loc=[http://www.logainm.ie/en/120 Gabhalmhaigh/Galmoy]}})\n</ref>\n<ref name=logainmCountyKilkenny>\n({{Harvnb|Fiontar|2008|loc=[https://www.logainm.ie/en/100006 County Cill Chainnigh/Kilkenny]}})\n</ref>\n<ref name=walshGalmoy>\n{{cite web|last1=Walsh|first1=Dennis|title=Barony of Galmoy|url=http://sites.rootsweb.com/~irlkik/history/galmoy.htm|website=ancestry.com}},\n{{cite web|last1=Walsh|first1=Dennis|title=The Baronies of Ireland|url=http://www.rootsweb.ancestry.com/~irlkik/ihm/baronie2.htm|website=ancestry.com}} and {{cite web|last1=Walsh|first1=Dennis|title=Barony Map of the Leinster Region|url=http://www.rootsweb.ancestry.com/~irlkik/ihm/barony-map-leinster.htm|website=ancestry.com}}.\n</ref>\n<ref name=downGalmoy>\n{{cite web|author1=Down Survey Project|title=Galmoy Map|url=http://downsurvey.tcd.ie/down-survey-maps.php#bm=Galmoy&c=Kilkenny&indexOfObjectValue=-1&indexOfObjectValueSubstring=-1|website=downsurvey.tcd.ie|publisher=The Down Survey Project}}\n</ref>\n<!-- Galmoy Geography -->\n<ref name=logainmGalmoySettlements>\n({{Harvnb|Fiontar|2008|loc=[http://www.logainm.ie/en/s?txt=in:120&cat=B Galmoy Towns]}} and {{Harvnb|Fiontar|2008|loc=[http://www.logainm.ie/en/s?txt=in:120&cat=ID Galmoy population centres]}})\n\n</ref>\n<!-- Galmoy Civil Parishes -->\n<ref nam